KwaZulu-Natal Transport MEC Mxolisi Kaunda says the taxi, which claimed 19 lives, is certified to carry only 16 passengers. JOHANNESBURG - The KwaZulu-Natal Transport MEC Mxolisi Kaunda says a taxi that crashed in Pietermaritzburg, killing 19 people, was overloaded.The taxi was transporting congregants to the KwaXimba area when the accident occurred.Eighteen people died on scene and one more, who was critically injured, died at the clinic.It's believed the taxi veered off a bridge and rolled down an embankment in the Msunduzi area.Kaunda says the vehicle is certified to carry 16 passengers but was ferrying 26 people, including the driver.Spokesperson Mluleki Mntungwa said, The MEC has asked the police and all other law enforcement agencies to launch a thorough and speedy investigation into this accident. 